# herdr-quicklook configuration (all optional).
# Copy this file as `.env` into the directory printed by:
#   herdr plugin config-dir herdr-quicklook
# Without a .env the plugin works with defaults; this file only ADDS lookup roots.

# QUICKLOOK_ROOTS: extra directories to try when a copied path does not exist
# under the current pane directory or repo. Colon-separated.
#
# The problem it solves: an agent prints `myrepo/docs/notes.md` but you are
# standing in a different repo. If all your repos live under ~/workspace,
# adding it here lets that path resolve to ~/workspace/myrepo/docs/notes.md.
#QUICKLOOK_ROOTS="$HOME/workspace:$HOME/src"
